{
  "stem": "19895.8",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I did contact relatives, including a name who this Schleyer in London gave to me, I wrote in London from Vienna.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I had difficulty how to communicate.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I had people to translate my letter.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I don't-- didn't speak German well enough to write letters.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I didn't speak English well enough.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So I always had some intermediary who helped me with my letter and contacting.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And this Mr.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Schleyer, gave me George Schleyer's name in New York, his brother, who also relative to my mother.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when I arrived to New York after being released from Camp Kilmer, I contacted.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Actually, I contacted them from Camp Kilmer, and he and another relative of mine, whom I didn't know about, but he knew about in New York-- again, second cousins or so-- were that couple and the older couple of the Schleyers, who he was in his late 70s, came to Camp Kilmer to visit me.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We couldn't converse, because they didn't speak a word of Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They were the German side of the family.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And my English was absolutely minimal.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So we had some, again, some interpreter who helped us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I keep up in knowing them and keep in touch, not only with the Manns-- M-A-N-N-- Dieter Mann and his wife, because the Schleyer were too old and they passed away.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And-- and I met also this cousin of my mother, Mrs.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Polachek, who is an interesting story of her own.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They were very successful people in the United States and we always hoped that someday we will see them and so on.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My marriage, a very happy one-- a very happy one.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My wife and I married 34 years.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] It was, as they say, [? bashert. ?] [?",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
